title: Stock Market News Review: SPY, QQQ Power Higher as Record Tariff Revenues Outweigh Concerning Retail Sales Data
summary: The S&P 500 ETF (SPY) and Nasdaq 100 ETF (QQQ) closed higher despite concerning retail sales and consumer sentiment data due to record tariff revenues and a soft Producer Price Index (PPI) report. U.S. net customs duties reached a record $31.4 billion in October. The Federal Reserve is anticipated to cut rates by 25 bps following the PPI report, while retail sales and consumer confidence showed weaker-than-expected figures, with the Consumer Confidence Index triggering a recession warning.
